{ By Reuters   Published:  15:29, 9 March 2019   https://www.dailymail.co.uk//wires/reuters/article-6789871/Rangers-reach-deal-G-Huska.html }
Goaltender Adam Huska agreed to an entry-level deal with the New York Rangers, the team announced on Saturday. Huska, 21, was a seventh-round selection by the Rangers in the 2015 NHL Entry Draft and has spent the last three seasons playing for the Connecticut Huskies. At Connecticut, Huska went 20-38-8, allowing 2.90 goals per game with a .908 save percentage. Before his college career, Huska played for the USHL's Green Bay Gamblers for part of 2014-15 and all of the following season. He was named the USHL top goalie in the latter season after going 26-9-2 with a 1.82 GAA, a .931 save percentage and four shutouts. --Field Level Media 
